<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Coriander Rice Recipe</title>
	<link href="~/css/corriondor.css" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Coriander Rice Recipe</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="recipe-container">
        
        <div class="ingredients">
            <h2>Ingredients</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>1 cup Basmati Rice</li>
                <li>2 cups Water</li>
                <li>1 cup Fresh Coriander Leaves</li>
                <li>1 Green Chili</li>
                <li>1-inch Ginger</li>
                <li>2 Garlic Cloves</li>
                <li>1 Onion (finely chopped)</li>
                <li>1 Tomato (finely chopped)</li>
                <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
                <li>1 Bay Leaf</li>
                <li>1/2 tsp Turmeric Powder</li>
                <li>2 tbsp Oil or Ghee</li>
                <li>Salt to taste</li>
                <li>Cashews & Fried Onions for garnish</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="instructions">
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Wash and soak the Basmati rice for 20 minutes, then drain.</li>
                <li>Grind coriander leaves, green chili, ginger, and garlic into a smooth paste.</li>
                <li>Heat oil in a pan and add cumin seeds and bay leaf.</li>
                <li>Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.</li>
                <li>Add tomatoes and cook until soft.</li>
                <li>Mix in turmeric powder and the coriander paste, cooking for 2 minutes.</li>
                <li>Add the soaked rice, salt, and water. Stir well.</li>
                <li>Cover and cook on low heat until the rice is fully cooked.</li>
                <li>Garnish with cashews and fried onions before serving.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </section>

</body>
</html>
